main event: A family of four reported seeing two unidentified flying objects moving rapidly over Elkins Park, Pennsylvania on February 9, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, flat, discs, approximately 8-10 feet in diameter and silvery in color.
The objects were observed moving rapidly in a northwesterly direction at an altitude of approximately 2,000 feet.
The sighting lasted for approximately 20-30 seconds.
The observers were deemed to be reliable and unexcited witnesses with no evidence of hoax or hallucination.
The witnesses were considered to be sane, normal individuals.
